        "# Problem Setup\n",
        "\n",
        "### Shake Smart Optimization Problem\n",
        "Shake Smart wants to optimize the production of four shake varieties: Berry Bliss, Tropical Delight, Mango Magic, and Green Zing.\n",
        "Each shake contributes differently to revenue and has specific ingredient requirements for fruit puree, yogurt, and honey.\n",
        "This problem will use linear programming to determine the optimal production plan to maximize revenue."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "cgswVE7UNGI8"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "#Import Libraries\n",
        "!pip install pulp\n",
        "from pulp import LpProblem, LpMaximize, LpVariable, lpSum"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "vfyhftnHGPg1",
        "outputId": "e2038700-a92f-4693-dadd-2dfa306825fd"
      },
      "execution_count": 6,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Requirement already satisfied: pulp in /usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages (2.9.0)\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Data Definition\n",
        "We define the parameters for the problem:\n",
        "- Shake types: ['Berry Bliss', 'Tropical Delight', 'Mango Magic', 'Green Zing']\n",
        "- Ingredient availability (ounces):\n",
        "  - Fruit puree: 16,000\n",
        "  - Yogurt: 5,000\n",
        "  - Honey: 3,500\n",
        "- Minimum production levels:\n",
        "  - Berry Bliss: 300\n",
        "  - Tropical Delight: 400\n",
        "  - Mango Magic: 500\n",
        "  - Green Zing: 600\n",
        "- Revenue per ounce:\n",
        "  - Berry Bliss: $1.8\n",
        "\n",
        "  - Tropical Delight: $2.4\n",
        "\n",
        "  - Mango Magic: $2.0\n",
        "  \n",
        "  - Green Zing: $3.0\n",
        "- Ingredient proportions:\n",
        "  - Berry Bliss: at least 12% yogurt, 8% honey\n",
        "  - Tropical Delight: at least 18% yogurt, 15% honey\n",
        "  - Mango Magic: at least 10% yogurt, 12% honey\n",
        "  - Green Zing: at least 20% yogurt, 10% honey"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "XdxNu1YpNXdE"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Code cell: Data Initialization\n",
        "# Data for the problem\n",
        "shake_types = ['Berry Bliss', 'Tropical Delight', 'Mango Magic', 'Green Zing']\n",
        "ingredient_availability = {\n",
        "    'fruit_puree': 16000,\n",
        "    'yogurt': 5000,\n",
        "    'honey': 3500\n",
        "}\n",
        "min_production = {\n",
        "    'Berry Bliss': 300,\n",
        "    'Tropical Delight': 400,\n",
        "    'Mango Magic': 500,\n",
        "    'Green Zing': 600\n",
        "}\n",
        "revenue_per_ounce = {\n",
        "    'Berry Bliss': 1.8,\n",
        "    'Tropical Delight': 2.4,\n",
        "    'Mango Magic': 2.0,\n",
        "    'Green Zing': 3.0\n",
        "}\n",
        "ingredient_proportions = {\n",
        "    'Berry Bliss': {'yogurt': 0.12, 'honey': 0.08},\n",
        "    'Tropical Delight': {'yogurt': 0.18, 'honey': 0.15},\n",
        "    'Mango Magic': {'yogurt': 0.10, 'honey': 0.12},\n",
        "    'Green Zing': {'yogurt': 0.20, 'honey': 0.10}\n",
        "}\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "GUKJXTRGNupZ"
      },
      "execution_count": 7,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Code cell: Define the Model\n",
        "# Create the problem\n",
        "problem = LpProblem(\"Maximize_Shake_Smart_Revenue\", LpMaximize)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Decision variables\n",
        "production = {shake: LpVariable(f\"Production_{shake}\", lowBound=0, cat='Continuous') for shake in shake_types}\n",
        "\n",
        "# Objective function\n",
        "problem += lpSum(revenue_per_ounce[shake] * production[shake] for shake in shake_types), \"Total_Revenue\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Constraints\n",
        "# Ingredient availability constraints\n",
        "problem += lpSum(production[shake] for shake in shake_types) <= ingredient_availability['fruit_puree'], \"Fruit_Puree_Constraint\"\n",
        "problem += lpSum(ingredient_proportions[shake]['yogurt'] * production[shake] for shake in shake_types) <= ingredient_availability['yogurt'], \"Yogurt_Constraint\"\n",
        "problem += lpSum(ingredient_proportions[shake]['honey'] * production[shake] for shake in shake_types) <= ingredient_availability['honey'], \"Honey_Constraint\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Minimum production constraints\n",
        "for shake in shake_types:\n",
        "    problem += production[shake] >= min_production[shake], f\"Min_Production_{shake}\"\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2af_-cD3Nzqg"
      },
      "execution_count": 8,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# Markdown cell: Solving the Problem\n",
        "\n",
        "### Solving the Optimization Problem\n",
        "We use the PuLP library to solve the linear programming model."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "g4TuLHuNN5cy"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Code cell: Solve the Model\n",
        "problem.solve()"
      ],
